The paper describes a generative autoencoder using implicit distributions, which is a topic commonly studied in the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses applications in computer vision (disentangling content and style information, image-to-image translation), which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as another likely sub-category. The use of implicit distributions for learning expressive posterior and conditional likelihood distributions also relates to topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions applications in semi-supervised classification and clustering, which are topics in natural language processing (cs.CL).
